By Igbaugba Ehigimetor Benin – The Edo National and State Assembly Election Petitions Tribunal sitting in Benin on Tuesday fixed June 10, for hearing in the petition filed by Zubairu Dada Abubakar of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP). Abubukar is challenging the election of Mr Ganiyu Audu of the All
Progressives Congress (APC) for the Etsako-West I Constituency in the
Edo State House of Assembly. At the sitting, counsel to Abubakar, Mr R. Isenalumhe, informed the
tribunal that his client planned to call 22 witnesses in the nine units
being challenged. Counsel to the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC), Mr
N. Okon, said he would call two witnesses but other witnesses might be
subpoenaed. The APC through its counsel, Mr M.I Afalokhai, said it would call 19 witnesses and one other on subpoena. Counsel to Audu, Mr C.I Aiguobaruoghian, said his client would call 19 witnesses and two others on subpoena. The Tribunal Chairman, Justice O. Ogundana, warned that there would
no extension of time beyond the 14 days allotted to the parties to call
their witnesses. Ogundana stressed that any witness found to be repeating evidence would be stopped.